er trial." Diabetes Care 26 (2003): 2268-74[4] ONTARGET Investigators, Yusuf S, Teo KK, et al "Telmisartan, ramipril, or both in patients at high risk for vascular events." N Engl J Med 358 (2008): 1547-59[5] National Kidney Foundation "KDOQI Clinical Practice Guideline for Diabetes and CKD: 2012 update." Am J Kidney Dis 60 (2012): 850-86[6] MHRA. Medicines and Healthcare Regulatory Agency "Combination use of medicines from different classes of renin-angiotensin system blocking agents: risk of hyperkalaemia, hypotension, and impaired renal function--new warnings. Available from: URL: http://www.mhra.gov.uk/Safetyinformation/DrugSafetyUpdate/" ([2014 June]):[7] Mann JF, Schmieder RE, McQueen M, et al. "Renal outcomes with telmisartan, ramipril, or both, in people at high vascular risk (the ONTARGET study): a multicentre, randomised, double-blind, controlled trial." Lancet 372 (2008): 547-53[8] "Product Information. Atacand (candesartan)." Astra Pharmaceuticals, Wayne, PA.[9] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[10] EMA. European Medicines Agency "PRAC recommends against combined use of medicines affecting the renin-angiotensin (RAS) system: recommendation will now be considered by CHMP for final opinion. Available from: URL: http://www.ema.europa.eu/docs/en_GB/document_library/Referrals_document/R" ([2014 Apr 11]):[11] Pfeffer MA, McMurray JJ, Velazquez EJ, et al. "Valsartan, captopril, or both in myocardial infarction complicated by heart failure, left ventricular dysfunction, or both." N Engl J Med 349 (2003): 1893-1906[12] Laverman GD, Navis G, Henning RH, De Jong PE, De Zeeuw D "Dual renin-angiotensin system blockade at optimal doses for proteinuria." Kidney Int 62 (2002): 1020-5[13] Jacobsen P, Andersen S, Jensen BR, Parving HH "Additive effect of ACE inhibition and angiotensin II receptor blockade in type I diabetic patients with diabetic nephropathy." J Am Soc Nephrol 14 (2003): 992-9[14] Guthrie RM "Review of ONTARGET: treating pat