ry excretion of furosemide in hypertensive subjects." J Clin Pharmacol 30 (1990): 538-42[15] "Product Information. Vasotec (enalapril)." Merck & Co, Inc, West Point, PA.[16] Good JM, Brady AJ, Noormohamed FH, Oakley CM, Cleland JG "Effect of intense angiotensin II suppression on the diuretic response to furosemide during chronic ACE inhibition." Circulation 90 (1994): 220-4[17] Champ JD "Case report: azotemia secondary to enalapril and diuretic use and the diagnosis of renovascular hypertension." Am J Med Sci 305 (1993): 25-7[18] Radley AS, Fitzpatrick RW "An evaluation of the potential interaction between enalapril and amiloride." J Clin Pharm Ther 12 (1987): 319-23[19] "Product Information. Aceon (perindopril)." Solvay Pharmaceuticals Inc, Marietta, GA.[20] "Product Information. Capoten (captopril)." Bristol-Myers Squibb, Princeton, NJ.[21] Lederle RM "Captopril and hydrochlorothiazide in the fixed combination multicenter trial." J Cardiovasc Pharmacol 7 (1985): S63-9[22] "Product Information. Zestrel (lisinopril)" Astra-Zeneca Pharmaceuticals, Wilmington, DE.[23] Lee HB, Blaufox MD "Renal functional response to captopril during diuretic therapy." J Nucl Med 33 (1992): 739-43[24] Ray K, Dorman S, Watson R "Severe hyperkalaemia due to the concomitant use of salt substitutes and ACE inhibitors in hypertension: a potentially life threatening interaction." J Hum Hypertens 13 (1999): 717-20[25] Good CB, McDermott L "Diet and serum potassium in patients on ACE inhibitors." JAMA 274 (1995): 538[26] "Product Information. Vasotec (enalapril)." Merck & Co, Inc, West Point, PA.', 1767363023);
